name: Galbraith Hall
about: Occupied in September 1965 in Revelle College, Galbraith Hall was UC San Diego’s first central library. Today the building’s primary occupants are the Center for Library & Instructional Services (CLICS) and the department of theatre and dance.
links: Dept. of Theater and Dance Page of Galbraith: http://theatre.ucsd.edu/facilities/theatres/galbraith.htm
